structured_output.prompt:
Produce a JSON object containing an array of products. Each product should have an `id` (integer), `name` (string), and `price` (float).

{
  "products": [
    {
      "id": "integer",
      "name": "string",
      "price": "float"
    }
  ]
}

Include at least two example products.

Create a JSON object describing a company, including its name and a nested address object. The address should contain `street` (string) and `city` (string).

{
  "company": {
    "name": "string",
    "address": {
      "street": "string",
      "city": "string"
    }
  }
}

Use 'Tech Solutions' for the company name, '123 Innovation Dr' for the street, and 'Metropolis' for the city.

Produce a JSON object representing a product catalog. The catalog should contain an array of items. Each item must have an `item_id` (string), `item_name` (string), a nested `details` object (containing `category` (string), `price` (float), `in_stock` (boolean)), and an array of `tags` (strings).

{
  "catalog": [
    {
      "item_id": "string",
      "item_name": "string",
      "details": {
        "category": "string",
        "price": "float",
        "in_stock": "boolean"
      },
      "tags": ["string"]
    }
  ]
}

Include at least one example item.
